COLLEGE ADMISSION PROCESS
Step 1: REGISTRATION - Register online through www.umak.edu.ph/olca/registration/new and print Application Form
Step 2: REQUIREMENT SUBMISSION - Report to Testing, Admission, & Scholarship Center (TASC) on the scheduled date to submit Application Form together with other admission test requirements.
RESIDENCY VERIFICATION >> Makati Resident Criteria: >> Graduate of any Public or Private High School in Makati City >> Registered Makati Voter >> Parent/Sibling is a registered Makati voter (if applicant is below 18 years old) >> Non-Makati Resident Criteria: >> Graduate of any non-Makati High School >> Non-Makati Voter >> Parent/Sibling is not a registered Makati voter (if applicant is below 18 years old)
Step 3: EXAMINATION FEE - Proceed to Cash Office to settle Php50.00 registration and testing fee and return to Testing, Admission, & Scholarship Center (TASC) to secure examination schedule and permit.
Step 4: ADMISSION TEST - Take the College Qualifying Examination based from the given schedule as seen on the Examination Permit.
COLLEGE QUALIFYING EXAMINATION (CQE) >> All Applicants for undergraduate admission are required to take the College Qualifying Examination. This examination covers English, Filipino, Mathematics, General Physics, Science, and General Information. >> Duration: 3 hours >> *Personality Test will be administered based on the request of the college (COAHS, COS)
Step 5: NOTICE OF ADMISSION - Upon passing the College Qualifying Examination, secure Notice of Admission (NOA) from the Testing, Admission, & Scholarship Center (TASC).
Step 6: COLLEGE INTERVIEW - Proceed to the college or center of the chosen program to secure Dean’s or Director’s approval of Notice of Admission.
Step 7: COURSE TAGGING - Return to Testing, Admission, & Scholarship Center (TASC) for course tagging to secure password for online enrollment.
Step 8: MEDICAL & DENTAL CLEARANCES - Secure a medical referral slip from the Medical & Dental Office (MDO). Submit X-ray result and proceed to Physical Examination after.
Step 9: ONLINE ENROLLMENT - To enroll, go to umak.edu.ph/olea and use the username and password issued by the Testing, Admission, & Scholarship Center (TASC). Print ADVISING SLIP and proceed to mode of payment from the website.
Step 10: REGISTRAR’S OFFICE - Present ADVISING SLIP to the Registrar’s Office to secure UMak email.
Step 11: iBAYAD - Print & present ASSESSMENT SLIP from the UMak email to any Makati City Barangay (iBayad). Wait for 3-4 days before going back to the Registrar’s Office to submit original complete admission requirements.
For College of Allied Health Studies - Proceed to Accounting Office
Step 12: COLLEGE ORIENTATION - Attend orientation based on the schedule provided by the college.
College Admission Test Procedure - 2020
To apply for the College Admission Test, here are the procedures: · Register online at www.umak.edu.ph/olca/registration/new and fill out the application form. · After answering the CAPTCHA, press submit and print the application form. · Report to the TASC office on the date reflected on the application form. Bring the following requirements for evaluation:
Accomplished Application Form · Four (4) copies of recent 2x2 ID pictures (with name tag and white background) · Photocopy of Report Card/Transcript of Records - Grade 11 Report Card (for current Grade 12 students) - Grade 12 Report Card (for SHS graduates) - Transcript of Records (for college transferees who have completed at least 2 years of tertiary education)
· Photocopy of PSA Birth Certificate · Photocopy of Voter’s ID/Certificate of Biological Parent/s or Sibling, if applicant is below 18yrs old · If complete, TASC office issues Examination Permit. Read the instructions and wait for the scheduled admission test. Only applicants with complete requirements will be entertained. · The Application Period will be from October 7, 2019 to November 27, 2019 · The Admission Test will be on March 1 & 8, 2020. · For more inquiries, email at tascinquiries@umak.edu.ph
